The paper discusses the conflict between machine learning and data obfuscation, which falls under the category of privacy and security in machine learning. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of differential privacy, which falls under the category of privacy-preserving data analysis, making cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) likely categories as well. Finally, the paper uses game theory to model the interaction between users and machine learners, which falls under the category of algorithmic game theory, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category as well.
